comment.undefined: It occurs before a larger seismic event(mainshock)
The art and science of preventing disease, prolonging life and promoting health through the organized efforts of society.
Natural Disaster is the consequence of a Natural Hazard(e.g volcanic eruption, earthquake or landslide) which affect human activities
It is a smaller earthquake that occurs after a previous large earthquake.
Flood is a state of higher water level along a river channel or on coast leading to inundation of land that is not normally submerge.

Due to Dam Breakage, the energy of the water stored behind the dam is capable of causing rapid
and unexpected flooding downstream, resulting in loss of life and great property damage.
It assigns a magnitude number to quantify the energy released by an earthquake.
A wave of energy that is generated by an earthquake or other earth vibration and that travels within the earth or along its surface
An accident, also known as an unintentional injury, is an undesirable, incidental and unplanned event.

valanche describes a quantity of snow or ice that slides down a mountainside under the force of gravity. It occurs if the load on the upper snow layers exceeds the bonding forces of the entire mass of snow. It often gathers material that is underneath the snowpack like soil, rock etc (debris avalanche).

A landslide is the movement of soil or rock controlled by gravity and the speed of the movement usually ranges between slow and rapid, but not very slow. It can be superficial or deep, but the materials have to make up a mass that is a portion of the slope or the slope itself. The movement has to be downward and outward with a free face.
ANatural Hazardis anaturallyoccurring event that might have a negative effect on people or the environment
The two sub-layers of the earth's crust (lithosphere) that move, float, and sometimes fracture and whose interaction causes continental drift, earthquakes, volcanoes, mountains, and oceanic trenches.
Sudden slipping or movement of a portion of the earth's crust, followed by a series of vibrations
Economic security as the ability of individuals, households or communities to cover their essential needs sustainably and with dignity.

Subsidence is the motion of the Earth's surface as it shifts downward relative to a datum (e.g. the sea level). Subsidence dry can be the result of: geological faulting, isostatic rebound, human impact (e.g. mining, extraction of natural gas) etc. Subsidence (wet) can be the result of: karst, changes in soil water saturation, permafrost degradation (thermokarst) etc.
Rockfall refers to quantities of rock or stone falling freely from a cliff face. It is caused by undercutting, weathering or permafrost degradation.
An instrument for automatically detecting and recording the intensity, direction, and duration of a movement of the ground, especially of an earthquake.
Hydrological disasters are defined as events caused by deviations in the normal water cycle and/or overflow of bodies of water caused by wind set-up.
It is defined as rainfall greater than 100 mm in 24 hours.
It is a sudden aggressive rainstorm falling for a short period of time.
